{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770831399,"nonce":"HZeNvE7Q9jBpttptgkXnQGXmUkM=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87qHSTZ","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/185","origin":"github"},"title":"worktree_remove.sh: false positive uncommitted changes warning for layer worktrees","message":"## Problem\n\nWhen removing a layer worktree, `worktree_remove.sh` runs `git status --porcelain` to check for uncommitted changes. However, for layer worktrees, `worktree_create.sh` adds symlinks (e.g., `platforms_ws`, `sensors_ws`) and directories (`core_ws/`, `.scratchpad/`) that are untracked from the workspace repo's perspective. This produces false positive warnings:\n\n```\n⚠️  Warning: Worktree has uncommitted changes:\n\n?? .scratchpad/\n?? core_ws/\n?? platforms_ws\n?? sensors_ws\n?? simulation_ws\n?? ui_ws\n?? underlay_ws\n```\n\nThis noise means a legitimate uncommitted change could easily be overlooked among the false positives, requiring `--force` to remove the worktree every time.\n\n## Proposed Fix\n\nFor layer worktrees, `worktree_remove.sh` should:\n\n1. **Clean up layer infrastructure first** -- remove symlinks, `.scratchpad/`, and the hybrid layer directory structure that `worktree_create.sh` created\n2. **Check inner package git worktrees** for uncommitted changes separately (e.g., `core_ws/src/unh_marine_autonomy` is its own git worktree with real work)\n3. **Then run `git status`** on the now-clean workspace worktree -- any remaining untracked files are genuinely uncommitted work\n4. **Prune inner package worktrees** during cleanup (currently the caller has to do this manually, as seen with `git worktree prune` needed after removal)\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `worktree_remove.sh` produces no false positive untracked file warnings for layer worktrees\n- [ ] Legitimate uncommitted changes in either the workspace worktree or inner package worktrees are still detected and warned about\n- [ ] Inner package git worktrees are pruned automatically during removal\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}